{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so summary can attribute statements to attendees.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: In-process mocks can miss real diarization label formats and handoff drift between STT output and summarization prompt. LLM-DEP + MULTI-STEP: correctness depends on real model outputs from both STT (speaker diarization) and LLM attribution in sequence, so minimum boundary is multi-agentic.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end test with a real multi-speaker meeting audio file and real STT+LLM calls. Assert transcript includes stable speaker labels and final structured summary attributes statements/tasks to the correct attendees using those labels.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Summary contains at least one action item for every attendee assigned a task.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: this is extraction/coverage quality from natural language, which depends on real LLM behavior and may vary across runs/prompts. Mocks would likely always pass schema checks while missing assignment recall failures.","test_description":"Use transcripts with known per-attendee task assignments and call the real summarization model. Validate each attendee with an assigned task has at least one corresponding action item in structured output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions appear in the dedicated \"decisions\" section, not only in narrative text.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: deciding what counts as a key decision and placing it in the correct section is model judgment/output quality, not just wiring. Pure mocks can hide misclassification/section-placement failures.","test_description":"Provide transcripts containing explicit decision statements, run real LLM summarization, and assert those decisions are present in the structured `decisions` field (not just freeform narrative).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"For audio longer than 60 minutes, service splits into segments, processes sequentially, and merges into one coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MOCK-MISS: local mocks can verify splitting logic but miss real long-audio STT behavior, segment boundary effects, and merge quality. MULTI-STEP: requires repeated model calls per segment plus synthesis step, i.e., chained agentic stages.","test_description":"Run with a real >60-minute recording. Assert segment creation and sequential processing order, then verify merged final summary is single structured output with consistent attendees, consolidated action items, and non-duplicated decisions across segments.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Full pipeline (upload audio -> transcribe -> summarize -> deliver structured output) completes automatically for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"REAL-INFRA + MULTI-STEP: this is true end-to-end behavior across file upload, external STT, LLM summarization, and output delivery. Multiple real agentic stages and system integrations must succeed without human intervention.","test_description":"Execute a production-like E2E run using a real meeting audio file and real external services. Verify successful completion status, no manual retries, and delivery of valid structured output containing attendees, action items, and decisions.","plan_consistent":t